The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Pujara, Dhiman in running

Colombo: India U-19 openers Cheteshwar Pujara and Gaurav Dhiman are the favourites for the man of the series award in the ICC U-19 World Cup here. 

Bangladesh captain Mushfiqur Rahim leads the standings with seven points. The wicketkeeper batsman is just one point clear of his Australian counterpart Moises Henriques and two Indians Pujara and Dhiman. 

All the three players are on six points in the man of the tournament standings. 

Dhiman and Pujara are Indias leading run-scorers in the tournament and have also shared the only two century opening stands in the all the 28 matches that have taken place so far, adding 147 against Namibia and 110 against the West Indies. 

Pujara scored 220 runs in the tournament with two half centuries to his credit. His highest is 97. 

Dhimans 174 runs also include two half centuries. The highest being 90. 

